Rating: 4
This recipe was super easy to make and it turned out delicious! I didn't have scallops so I doubled the shrimp. You can adjust how spicy the dish is with the amount of chile paste you use. I used Huy Fong, Sriracha Hot Chili Sauce and since I don't like my food with a ton of spice I stuck to the recommended dose. It added a lot of flavor, but wasn't too spicy. Even with doubling the recipe it only made enough food to feed three hungry adults. We were all very disappointed that there weren't any leftovers for lunch the next day!

