Rating: 4
I, too, made some substitutions, but this was truly an award-winning recipe. I would like to suggest my way to treat eggplant, when using similar recipes. I coat well a rimmed cookie sheet (or similar pan) with olive oil and place the rounds of eggplant in it. I then brush a nice film of olive oil on top and broil them until nicely browned. I turn them without adding more oil and brown them nicely. They are then ready to use in anything and haven't absorbed a lot of oil. This has worked for me for years and has saved me a lot of time, effort, and oil!

